702627f-a.text:
(1)
Nineteenth Ave, east side, at the N.E. corner of 86th Street. A view of the Van Pelt Manor, which once owned the surrounding land, under a Dutch grant. It was at 1873-86th Street. It was bought by the City of New York in 1925, for $4,000, and moved. Now 3-story brick homes
occupy the site.
1922.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
(2)
The same, another angle.
1922.
